article.headline: Lipscomb 79, Stetson 68
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Eddie Ard scored 25 points to lead Lipscomb to a 79-68 win over Stetson on Sunday night. Lipscomb (9-7) made the first goal of the night and never trailed, shooting 53 percent to Stetson's 45 percent. Lipscomb was up by eight points at the half, leading 36-28, and the team's shooting only improved in the second half. A couple of late 3-pointers for Stetson (5-9) could only bring the team within nine points of Lipscomb with 2:07 remaining. Trey Williams added 16 points for Lipscomb, and Jason Hopkins had 10. For Stetson, Kris Thomas and Garfield Blair both scored 11 points, and Gabe McMillen and Tim Lang each added 10.
